	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Hello? This should have been fixed years ago.

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bpvpm11462_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('11462');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm11462','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('11462');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm11462','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=127299'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
KlimRuos</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 1<br>
				
				Registered: 12-26-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=127299'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=11462#M11462">1</a> of 9
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1575 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Being a hardcore pvper for the most part myself, I've come to notice numerous problem that hinder my class' ability to efficiently compete in pvp with other high end geared players. I browsed some of the threads and saw some of the same problems I've seen, but figured I'd profess my own views on these particular issues myself since nothing appears to be improving, or looks as if it's in the process of being fixed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So anyways, I play a wizard, but I'm speaking for all casters in general, since it isn't a class specific thing itself exactly. As I already saw, melees have a huge advantage versus casters in pvp. Why, you may ask? There is several reasons. First, there has been nerfs placed on casters over the years to balance casters vs. melee, but it has done the exact opposite. First, no&nbsp;single nuke, for any caster, can do more than 66% of its original damage, not including resists. So, an anguish+ geared melee for example probably has close or above 500+ in all resists unbuffed. If I were to duel a 15k unbuffed warrior with similar resists, and&nbsp; my lure (lands more often for those of you who aren't wizards) spell does about 1500 base damage. 66% of 1500 is roughly 1000 damage. So, if every nuke landed for full damage (which is impossible) I could kill that warrior in 15 nukes. It sounds easy, but it's not. Infact, my best lure usually lands for 400-600 dmg on high geared people. The thing about this I find disturbing is that there is no nerf on melees. Melees dish out 100% of their damage output, while casters dish out 66% of theirs....does that make a bit of sense? Hell no it doesn't. Either nerf melees so their melee is 66% of their regular output, or release the nerf off casters.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also, another nerf was placed on casters., except this one is a little more fun! The nerf itself does not allow a nuke to do more than 40% of any one person's health per cast. Basically, if I were to attack a lvl 1 wizard in pvp, who had 10 hps, it would take me 3 casts to kill a lvl 1 (keep in mind I'm a lvl 70 wizard). Even if i casted my 5800ish nuke on the lvl one, and it landed, it is not possible for it to do more than 4 dmg to a lvl 1. Fun, huh? Yet, melees can walk up and kill a lvl 1 instantly. My point, however,&nbsp;is not about how long it takes a lvl 1 or not, but rather the issue of nerfs on casters. Specifically, since I'm a wizard, I have the ability manaburn. This nerf does not allow me to do more than 40% of someone's health. Yet, a rogue can walk up and backstab me for a huge amount and do well over 40% of my hps, how is that fair? That's right, it's not, and thus why it needs to be fixed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our resists have always been a big part of EQ, but does it disadvantage casters in pvp? See, melees, just like casters, can resist spells in pvp obviously. But, can casters resists hits? Nope, we can't. Infact, I don't see a listing in my inventory saying how high my resists are to 1h blunt, slashing, piercing, etc. Is this fair? I certainly don't think it is. And don't argue that AA's provide dmg avoidance mitigation, because those are not a natural stat from an item like spell resists are. From my point of view, to balance this, either the integration of a new resist listing in our inventories for weapons is needed(which I see as highly unneeded personally), or casters' natural dmg avoidance/mitigation needs to be increased equal to that of how spell resists are, otherwise melees have an outright advantage over casters, and it isn't just a small advantage either.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I've found it increasingly hard to beat high end melees as a wizards because of these issues. I'm anguish geared, and I can barely beat melees who are qvic geared. This is ridiculous, because my skill is far superior to a lot of people I duel or fight in pvp and I still lose most the time to melees simply because of the nerfs on my class that&nbsp;hinder my ability to defeat my opponent efficiently. Pvp isn't like it used to be at the beginning of EQ, where skill was a huge determinant in who would win duels. Skill now adays is basically irrelevant and is all gear and class depedant. But, to basically put this, spells just don't land as they should. Casters in general just cannot land spells to match that of a melees dmg output, and I've listed the reasons why. </DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>12-26-2005</span> <span class=time_text>10:38 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
