<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/troll.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=11466#M11466">3</a> of 9
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1426 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			[quote]So anyways, I play a wizard, but I'm speaking for all casters in general, since it isn't a class specific thing itself exactly. As I already saw, melees have a huge advantage versus casters in pvp. Why, you may ask? There is several reasons. First, there has been nerfs placed on casters over the years to balance casters vs. melee, but it has done the exact opposite. First, no single nuke, for any caster, can do more than 66% of its original damage, not including resists. So, an anguish+ geared melee for example probably has close or above 500+ in all resists unbuffed. If I were to duel a 15k unbuffed warrior with similar resists, and  my lure (lands more often for those of you who aren't wizards) spell does about 1500 base damage. 66% of 1500 is roughly 1000 damage. So, if every nuke landed for full damage (which is impossible) I could kill that warrior in 15 nukes. It sounds easy, but it's not. Infact, my best lure usually lands for 400-600 dmg on high geared people. The thing about this I find disturbing is that there is no nerf on melees. Melees dish out 100% of their damage output, while casters dish out 66% of theirs....does that make a bit of sense? Hell no it doesn't. Either nerf melees so their melee is 66% of their regular output, or release the nerf off casters.[/quote]<br><br>I'm not 100% certian but I do believe that melees were nerfed to 66% in PVP.<br><br>[quote]Also, another nerf was placed on casters., except this one is a little more fun! The nerf itself does not allow a nuke to do more than 40% of any one person's health per cast. Basically, if I were to attack a lvl 1 wizard in pvp, who had 10 hps, it would take me 3 casts to kill a lvl 1 (keep in mind I'm a lvl 70 wizard). Even if i casted my 5800ish nuke on the lvl one, and it landed, it is not possible for it to do more than 4 dmg to a lvl 1. Fun, huh? Yet, melees can walk up and kill a lvl 1 instantly. My point, however, is not about how long it takes a lvl 1 or not, but rather the issue of nerfs on casters. Specifically, since I'm a wizard, I have the ability manaburn. This nerf does not allow me to do more than 40% of someone's health. Yet, a rogue can walk up and backstab me for a huge amount and do well over 40% of my hps, how is that fair? That's right, it's not, and thus why it needs to be fixed.[/quote]<br><br>Use a rain spell to kill the level 1 or *GASP* pull out a dagger and stab them... I love it how people compare level 70 PVP to level 1. Do you know WHY the 40% nerf was put in place? Because wizards (and Necros) were 1-shot killing people with manaburn and lifeburn and getting like 3-5k crit nukes in PVP. Yes the rogue can walk up to you and backstab you for huge damage, but can he do that from 300 /loc units away? no...<br><br>[quote]Our resists have always been a big part of EQ, but does it disadvantage casters in pvp? See, melees, just like casters, can resist spells in pvp obviously. But, can casters resists hits? Nope, we can't. Infact, I don't see a listing in my inventory saying how high my resists are to 1h blunt, slashing, piercing, etc. Is this fair? I certainly don't think it is. And don't argue that AA's provide dmg avoidance mitigation, because those are not a natural stat from an item like spell resists are. From my point of view, to balance this, either the integration of a new resist listing in our inventories for weapons is needed(which I see as highly unneeded personally), or casters' natural dmg avoidance/mitigation needs to be increased equal to that of how spell resists are, otherwise melees have an outright advantage over casters, and it isn't just a small advantage either.[/quote]<br><br>Open up your skills box... Look under DEFENSE, DODGE, PARRY, BLOCK, RIPOSTE... These are your resistances to 1hb/1hs/piercing...Its not our fault you quad kited to level 70... As for teh AAs that provide damage mitigation and advoidance to melee hits... I dont see any AAs that provide spell shielding, dot shielding, ect... which is the direct equivalant to these AAs. Also a very easy and 100% effective way to avoid melee damage is run out of range! Now all you have to **SMURF** about are Rangers bowing you for 500+ a pop from long range. Its pretty impossible for a melee to you know run out of casting range esp with those focus items.<br><br>[quote]I've found it increasingly hard to beat high end melees as a wizards because of these issues. I'm anguish geared, and I can barely beat melees who are qvic geared. This is ridiculous, because my skill is far superior to a lot of people I duel or fight in pvp and I still lose most the time to melees simply because of the nerfs on my class that hinder my ability to defeat my opponent efficiently. Pvp isn't like it used to be at the beginning of EQ, where skill was a huge determinant in who would win duels. Skill now adays is basically irrelevant and is all gear and class depedant. But, to basically put this, spells just don't land as they should. Casters in general just cannot land spells to match that of a melees dmg output, and I've listed the reasons why.[/quote]<br><br>Well gee, no duh... An equally geared melee should be able to pwn a caster hardcore if they get in range. All you uber people are just now reaping the benefits of mudflation that have been hitting the casual gamer over the head for years.<br><br>Skill hasnt been a determining factor in EQ PVP since late velious/early POP its been all about the gear. Please as someone who is 'anguish geared' go ahead and tell me its all a lie and that all your PVP was 'skillz'. I need a laugh today. What about all those expansions where melees could not get in range of casters to utilize their damage output? What that time when casters could 'ghost' oh so easily and nuke a melee into oblivion? What about the resist changes made to suck up to the ubers? Oh now you cant resist snare with 150 MR, you need to have like 400 MR... And ofcourse the mudflation, of everyone wanting bigger, better weapons, bigger better spells, bigger better pets and bigger better loot... You made your bed now lie in it.I've found it increasingly hard to beat high end melees as a wizards because of these issues. I'm anguish geared, and I can barely beat melees who are qvic geared. This is ridiculous, because my skill is far superior to a lot of people I duel or fight in pvp and I still lose most the time to melees simply because of the nerfs on my class that hinder my ability to defeat my opponent efficiently. Pvp isn't like it used to be at the beginning of EQ, where skill was a huge determinant in who would win duels. Skill now adays is basically irrelevant and is all gear and class depedant. But, to basically put this, spells just don't land as they should. Casters in general just cannot land spells to match that of a melees dmg output, and I've listed the reasons why.	
		</td></tr>
