<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=11765#M11765">9</a> of 9
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 455 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			PVP has been broken from a melee/offensive caster perspective for quite some time.<br><br>Here is a wierd idea (and I am sure it will catch criticism):<br><br>1) Take each of the weapon damage types (1hs, 2hs, 1hb, 2hb, 1hp, 2hp) and match each one with a resist type if you melee a caster. So you end up with:<br>a) 1hs + 2hp = magic<br>b) 2hs = cold<br>c) 1hb = fire<br>d) 2hb = poison<br>e) 1hp = disease<br><br>So if a melee hits a caster, apply the resists of the caster instead of the AC , avoidance, etc.<br><br>2) Against a caster, the slower the weapon swing, the higher the resist mod. So make the resist number negative to the atk delay. If the atk delay is 20, then apply neg 20. If it is 50, apply neg 50.<br><br>I am sure these modified rules for hitting an offensive caster might need some modification. But this is just a proposal. Try this for 2 weeks in a couple zones and see what happens.<br><br>I think the playerbase might rethink how crippling resists are as a result of this and perhaps the pvp ruleset might get changed. As is now, there is just not enough casters left to overcome any of the naysayers who will undoubtedly be the melee.<br><br>Shoot away, I am sure this will draw criticism galore. But at least it is a proposal instead of a complaint. Unfortunately, too many folks are afraid to step out with ideas as they usually get shot down by the frequent posters who critique everything but propose nothing.<br>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
